page.title: 02Life styles
page.content: The hamlet of Sewards End is around 400 years old. The houses lie generally off one road. Most people are friendly but some adults aren't very co-operative. In Sewards End there are a few amenities consisting of a Public House and an Agricultural Store. Most of the land is fields but a lot is gardens. There are lots of different kinds of trees in the area. The most common kind is deciduous but there is also some pine. Many people have lived in Sewards End for up to forty years but recently people have moved in. The majority of the people that live in Sewards End are either retired or are commuters.
